---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../styles/pages/about.css";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Kat and what this site is for." mainClass="about-page" variantFonts>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="about-intro">
    <p class="about-eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="about-name">KAT</h1>
    <p class="about-handle">A Kat's Kronicles &middot; Since 2022</p>

    <blockquote class="about-lede">
      I write about games the way I wish more people wrote about games &mdash; from inside the experience, not above it.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="about-prose">
      <p>
        This site started as a place to put thoughts that were too long for social media and too personal
        for anywhere else. It's still that, mostly. I care about narrative-driven games, systems that say
        something, and the specific feeling of finishing something and not knowing quite what to do with
        yourself afterward.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm not a professional critic. I don't get review copies most of the time, and I'm not trying to
        be first. I'm trying to write pieces that are worth reading six months after a game comes out,
        because most of what I have to say doesn't arrive until I've had time to sit with it.
      </p>
      <p>
        My GOTY picks lean hard into <em>JRPGs and narrative RPGs</em> &mdash; Xenoblade Chronicles 3,
        Persona 5 Royal, Metaphor: ReFantazio. That tells you most of what you need to know about my taste.
        I have a high tolerance for slow starts and a low tolerance for bad final acts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-socials">
      <a class="about-social-link" href="#">
        <span class="about-social-label">Twitter / X</span>
        <span class="about-social-arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="#">
        <span class="about-social-label">Backloggd</span>
        <span class="about-social-arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="#">
        <span class="about-social-label">Steam</span>
        <span class="about-social-arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="/rss.xml">
        <span class="about-social-label">RSS Feed</span>
        <span class="about-social-arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="about-stats" aria-label="Site statistics">
    <div class="about-stat">
      <span class="about-stat-number">24</span>
      <span class="about-stat-label">Reviews Published</span>
      <span class="about-stat-note">2022 &ndash; present</span>
    </div>
    <div class="about-stat">
      <span class="about-stat-number">4</span>
      <span class="about-stat-label">GOTY Picks</span>
      <span class="about-stat-note">one per year, no ties</span>
    </div>
    <div class="about-stat">
      <span class="about-stat-number">~800</span>
      <span class="about-stat-label">Hours Logged</span>
      <span class="about-stat-note">tracked, not counting replays</span>
    </div>
    <div class="about-stat">
      <span class="about-stat-number">5</span>
      <span class="about-stat-label">Currently Playing</span>
      <span class="about-stat-note">always too many</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Middle: content + sidebar -->
  <section class="about-middle">
    <div class="about-content">
      <p class="about-section-eyebrow">The Site</p>
      <h2 class="about-section-title">What You'll Find Here</h2>

      <div class="about-content-prose">
        <p>
          Everything on this site is written from direct experience. I don't cover games I haven't finished.
          I don't write about a game's release week unless I have something to say that couldn't have been said later.
        </p>
        <p>
          The formats I use are chosen because they let the writing go somewhere, rather than ticking boxes.
          A review doesn't need a score. A boss feature doesn't need to be a guide. An essay doesn't need
          to cover every angle.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-formats">
        <div class="about-format-item">
          <div class="about-format-type"><span>Reviews</span></div>
          <div class="about-format-desc">Long-form, first-person, written after completion. Follows your experience rather than a checklist. No scores.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-format-item">
          <div class="about-format-type"><span>Boss Features</span></div>
          <div class="about-format-desc">A close reading of one fight &mdash; mechanics, mood, and what the encounter says about the game around it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-format-item">
          <div class="about-format-type"><span>I'm Excited</span></div>
          <div class="about-format-desc">Short pieces on upcoming games. Not previews &mdash; just honest anticipation, before I know if it earns it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-format-item">
          <div class="about-format-type"><span>Essays</span></div>
          <div class="about-format-desc">Longer thinking on a topic, a pattern, or a question a game opened up that one review couldn't close.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="about-sidebar">
      <!-- Favourites -->
      <div class="about-sidebar-block">
        <div class="about-sidebar-head">
          <span class="about-sidebar-pip"></span>
          <span class="about-sidebar-head-text">All-Time Favourites</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">01</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Xenoblade Chronicles 3</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2022</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">02</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Persona 5 Royal</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2019</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">03</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Nier: Automata</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2017</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">04</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Metaphor: ReFantazio</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2024</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">05</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Hollow Knight</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2017</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-fav-item">
          <span class="about-fav-rank">06</span>
          <span class="about-fav-title">Xenoblade Chronicles 2</span>
          <span class="about-fav-year">2017</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Taste profile -->
      <div class="about-sidebar-block">
        <div class="about-sidebar-head">
          <span class="about-sidebar-pip lavender"></span>
          <span class="about-sidebar-head-text">Taste Profile</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-taste-cloud">
          <span class="about-tag strong">Narrative RPG</span>
          <span class="about-tag strong">Turn-Based</span>
          <span class="about-tag mid">Metroidvania</span>
          <span class="about-tag mid">Soulslike</span>
          <span class="about-tag strong">JRPG</span>
          <span class="about-tag">Open World</span>
          <span class="about-tag mid">Action RPG</span>
          <span class="about-tag">Strategy</span>
          <span class="about-tag strong">Slow Starts</span>
          <span class="about-tag">Character Writing</span>
          <span class="about-tag mid">Long Games</span>
          <span class="about-tag strong">Bad Final Acts</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom: philosophy + contact -->
  <section class="about-bottom">
    <div>
      <p class="about-section-eyebrow">The Writing</p>
      <h2 class="about-section-title">How I Think About This</h2>
      <div class="about-bottom-prose">
        <p>
          I try to write about the experience of playing a game rather than the game as an object to evaluate.
          That means I'm less interested in whether something is "good" in the abstract and more interested in
          what it actually felt like to be inside it.
        </p>
        <p>
          I don't separate mechanics from narrative in my writing because I don't think they're separate in
          the experience. When a boss fight lands emotionally, that's a design achievement. When the pacing
          breaks something that was working, that's a writing failure. The line between them is usually imaginary.
        </p>
        <p>
          I have opinions. I'll give them. But I'd rather persuade you with a specific example than a declaration,
          and I'd rather the piece be worth reading even if you disagree with where it lands.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="about-section-eyebrow">Reach Out</p>
      <h2 class="about-section-title">Get in Touch</h2>
      <div class="about-bottom-prose">
        <p>
          I'm not hard to find. If a piece resonated, or if you think I got something badly wrong, I want to
          hear it. The best conversations I've had about games started with someone disagreeing with me politely.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm not currently taking sponsored posts, affiliate arrangements, or early access in exchange for
          coverage. If that changes, I'll say so clearly at the top of anything it touches.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-contact-block">
        <p class="about-contact-label">Contact</p>
        <p class="about-contact-text">
          The best way to reach me is on Twitter / X. I check it more than I should.
          For longer things, there's an email in the RSS feed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
